# Vue Component Conventions

## Script Setup

- Always use `<script setup lang="ts">` — no Options API
- Use typed `defineProps` with TypeScript interfaces
- Import types from `~/types/` using `import type`

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import type { Experience } from "~/types/cv";

const props = defineProps<{
	items: Experience[];
}>();
</script>
```

## Component Organization

- `base/` — thin wrappers around Nuxt UI components (e.g., `BaseButton`, `BaseCard`)
- `cv/` — data-driven CV section components (e.g., `CvExperience`, `CvEducation`)
- Nuxt auto-imports components by directory: `BaseBadge`, `CvHeader`, etc.

## Auto-Imports

Nuxt auto-imports composables, components, and utils — do NOT manually import:
- Composables: `useColorMode`, `useRoute`, `useSeoMeta`, `ref`, `computed`, `watch`, `onMounted`
- Components: all components in `app/components/`
- Utils: all exports from `app/utils/`

## Icons

Use string-based icon names with Nuxt Icon:
- Heroicons: `i-heroicons-briefcase`, `i-heroicons-sun`
- Simple Icons: `i-simple-icons-github`, `i-simple-icons-linkedin`
